Description: We are a mobile advertising solution that drives brand lift for businesses.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: We are a mobile advertising solution that drives brand lift for businesses. Brands that want to serve ads in mobile games use our platform to create advertisements that we deliver through opensource SDKs.  We're special because in our unique advertising model, each image or video is presented with a multiple choice question that users are incentivized to answer correctly to claim in-app rewards - premium content, bonus features, disabled banner ads, etc. We believe that this question model is better because it doesn't create a break in activity for consumers (unlike standard video ads which leave you with nothing to do while you watch) and provides meaningful engagement (unlike banner ads which we are trained to ignore). Why are we doing this? Because we're developers. And the developer community needs relief from current ad platforms that don't care enough to offer transparent revenue or proper documentation. We want to make app monetization easy and rewarding for people like us.

Description: Roark Travel Club is part of the Shepherd of the Hills Entertainment Group, offering beautifully unique vacations at a fraction of the cost.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Roark Travel Club is an international travel company that offers the opportunity for tourists and leisure travelers to visit thousands of destinations all over the world. The company has been in business for almost a decade, during which time it has attracted a healthy clientele with its low rates, quality service, and extensive choice of top travel destinations. The company also offers regular discounts on travel packages, making it possible for more people to travel to places that they wouldn’t be able to visit otherwise.   One of the most distinctive features of the Club is its “pay-as-you-play” travel program that greatly reduces the cost of resort accommodations. Resulting in lower overall costs compared to regular club pricing, travelers on a budget are able to enjoy lower rates on accommodations at even the most exclusive resorts. And with 2,500 resort options all over the world, the lower rates make it more affordable for travelers to add more vacation destinations to their itineraries if they wish.   The Club offers an extensive selection of travel destinations, including tropical islands, famous beach destinations, majestic snow-covered peaks, awe-inspiring deserts and lakes, world famous amusement attractions, and even ancient cities in some of the world’s cradles of civilization. The company offers a much broader range of destinations than most other travel firms, giving families and individuals more options to plan out the type of vacation they wish.   The Club offers a membership program that provides a number of significant perks exclusive to members. Signing up gives members the opportunity to stay updated on new travel offers and destinations as they are made available, by way of informational publications sent directly to their email addresses. Roark Travel Club members also receive discount offers and invitations to special savings programs that add even more value to the travel packages offered.   Roark has been providing travelers with the opportunity to save on travel costs for more than 9 years by way of its exclusive membership programs. These offers have helped boost the company’s clientele significantly, with membership now over the 9,000 mark. The cost of membership itself is very affordable, and the perks made available exclusively to members provide even more value to the company’s services.   The Club goes beyond the standard travel packages offered by other firms by providing VIP treatment for all club members. The company strives to ensure that the highest quality of service is provided, with all the conveniences and amenities necessary for an enjoyable stay made available. The company was established with the goal of providing superior value for the money, and every effort is made to make this apparent in every aspect of its service. With Roark Travel Club’s VIP treatment, guests are able to enjoy a level of service typical of the most exclusive clubs and hotel accommodations.   This quality of service extends to the booking process as well. All of the Club members are given priority booking in each and every one of the company’s network of resorts. This ensures that guests are able to visit any of the 2,500 resorts that the company is affiliated with, as well as enjoy a more convenient and hassle-free travel experience.   There are a number of key features provided by the Club that isn't available anywhere else. All customer concerns are ably handled by the company’s Branson Hotline service, which gives guests a direct line to friendly and accommodating customer support staff. Well-trained and extensively experienced, this team ensures the very best quality of customer service possible.   Fitness buffs who wish to stay in shape throughout their vacations will be able to do so by way of the company’s Club Roark health club membership, which is provided at no extra charge in most of the travel destinations on offer. This feature ensures that guests have access to weight lifting equipment, saunas, tanning beds, indoor pools, kiddy pools, and much more while on vacation.   Many of the Roark's travel destinations are exclusive offers only available to club members. An example is Emerald Pointe, which provides travelers with a unique opportunity to visit one of the last remaining open areas of land on Table Rock Lake. With its majestic views, expansive wooded lots, and close proximity to modern conveniences, the area not only serves as an ideal spot to visit while on vacation, but a worthy option to consider for future settlement in the future as well.   Roark Travel Club also provides guests with exclusive access to the company’s own vacation resort, which is ideally situated on the picturesque banks of Lake Taneycomo. Located in the heart of breathtaking Ozark Mountain Country, the lake is only a few minutes’ drive away from the tourist attractions at Branson. Nevertheless, it offers a distinctively small town atmosphere that makes it an excellent spot for travel and leisure. Boasting of an outdoor swimming pool and boating and fishing facilities, Lake Taneycomo is one of the most popular stops on a Roark Travel Club vacation.   Those with a taste for adrenaline-fueled adventures will definitely want to check out Roark Travel Club’s Vigilante Extreme ZipRider. The ride begins atop a 230-foot observation tower, which guests reach via a glass elevator that offers a stunning view of the surrounding countryside. From there, guests have the choice of one of four zip lines, each of which whisks them downhill over 160 acres of historic homestead. Only for the bravest of adrenaline-junkies, the ZipRider is one of Roark Travel Club’s most memorable attractions.   Other exclusive Roark Travel Club attractions are the Trail of Lights in Branson, Missouri, which takes guests through a breathtaking drive through an animated Christmas display; the Shepherd of the Hills stage performance held every night; and the Christmas on the Trail attraction, with its unique Cowboy Christmas feature. The Shepherd of the Hills is an especially impressive feature, with more than 80 actors, 40 horse, a flock of sheep, and authentic turn of the century props giving life to the celebrated Harold Bell Wright-penned epic tale.

Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Experience, focus, dedication and integrity in a caring atmosphere: That’s what you can expect from the entire team at The Snow Law Firm. We pursue your case objectives with the attention they deserve, giving you top quality, professional representation from pre-suit through trial or settlement. The Snow Law Firm draws on the strength and experience of a team of attorneys and other legal experts to provide clients with reliable, caring and confidential advice and direction. We proudly serve with integrity and a strong sense of justice, ensuring a strong voice is serving you. Firm principal Corbin Snow, III is a graduate of St. Mary’s Law School in San Antonio, Texas and is Board Certified in Personal Injury Trial Law. Licensed to practice law since 1989, he also focuses on eminent domain and condemnation law. Corbin is an active member of the San Antonio Bar Association and is currently a Director of the San Antonio Bar Association. Corbin is a San Antonio native. He attended San Antonio Academy, Deerfield Academy in Deerfield, MA and majored in religious studies at Vanderbilt University, where he graduated with a Bachelor of Arts degree. Upon returning to San Antonio, he attended St. Mary’s University School of Law and received his Doctorate of Jurisprudence in 1988. While at St. Mary’s, Corbin served as Chairman of the Board of Advocates and was selected to the Order of Barristers. Corbin began his legal career with the firm of Plunkett, Gibson, and Allen, in the area of insurance defense. In 1991, he began representing injured individuals and landowners. A member of the American Board of Trial Advocates, Corbin is also a member of the San Antonio Bar Foundation and a Life Fellow of the Texas Bar Foundation. Corbin remains active in his church and in several non-profit organizations. He and his wife, Elizabeth, have four sons.
